place.name: WICKEN
place.gazetteerText: WICKEN, a parish in Potterspury district, Northampton; 3½ miles WSW of Stony-Stratford, and 5 WSW of Wolverton r. station. It has a post-office under Stony-Stratford. Acres, 2,280. Real property, £2,671. Pop., 529. Houses, 101. The manor belongs to SirMordaunt, Bart. W. Park is the seat of Lord Penrhyn. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Peterborough. Value, £500.* Patron, SirMordaunt, Bart. The church is good; and there are a national school and charities £22. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
